Package main

Class GeneralSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.GeneralSettings
  • public class GeneralSettings
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains general settings for various classes. Rather than hard coding a value a setting should be added to this file to make it easier to find the value and change it in the future.

    • Method Detail

      • updateAspectRatio

        public static void updateAspectRatio​(int width,
                                     int height)
        Calculates the current OpenGL coordinate system scaling factor for a certain width and height of the window. The result will be <1, 1> if the width and height are 1280 and 720 respectively. Larger screen values will result in a smaller scale factor in that axis.
        Parameters:
        width - the width of the screen in pixels.
        height - the height of the screen in pixels.

      • getAspectRatio

        public org.lwjgl.util.vector.Matrix2f getAspectRatio()
        Retrieves the current OpenGL coordinate system scaling factor. The result will be <1, 1> if the #DISPLAY_WIDTH and #DISPLAY_HEIGHT are 1280 and 720 respectively. Larger screen values will result in a smaller scale factor in that axis.
        Returns:
        The 2x2 matrix which will scale an element in such a way to appear right with the current screen size.

      • initializeFonts

        public static void initializeFonts()
        Loads the default font for use in rendering texts.
